
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `login` baraye vorood be hesabe karbari (user account) dar system estefade mishavad. Agar shoma aslan vared nashodeid, ya agar az hesab kharej shodeid, `login` az shoma username va password mikhad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `login` --> 🔑 Vorood ba username va password (sade tareen halat)
    🔹 `login -f username` --> 🚪 Bypass kardan darkhast dobare username (agar ghablan vared shodeid)

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ login

    🔹 System username va password mikhad.

    $ login -f ali

    🔹 System be tor mostaghim password ali ro mikhad (age az ghabl vared shode bood).

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ login
    username: jafar
    password:
    Last login: Tue Oct 27 10:00:00 PDT 2023 on tty1

    🔹 In mesal neshon mide ke system username `jafar` ro darkhast karde, va shoma password khodetoon ro vared mikonid. Agar dorost bashe, shoma be hesabetoon vared mishavid.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `login` command is used to log in to a user account on the system. If you are not already logged in, or if you have logged out, `login` will prompt you for a username and password.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `login` --> 🔑 Log in with username and password (simplest form)
    🔹 `login -f username` --> 🚪 Bypass the username prompt (if you were already logged in)

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ login

    🔹 The system will prompt for a username and password.

    $ login -f alice

    🔹 The system will directly prompt for Alice's password (if she was previously logged in).

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ login
    username: bob
    password:
    Last login: Tue Oct 27 10:00:00 PDT 2023 on tty1

    🔹 This example shows the system prompting for the username `bob`, and you entering your password. If correct, you will be logged in to your account.
